## üë§ User Help Guides

### Creating a Project

**Navigation Path:**
```
Home tab ‚Üí "+" button (center-left in tab bar) ‚Üí Choose method
```

**View Components:**
- Tab Selection: Set `selectedTab = .createProject` to show `CreateProjectSelectionView()`
- AI Option: Navigate to `ConversationalAIForm()` (sheet or NavigationLink)
- Manual Option: Navigate to `ManualProjectForm()` or `ProjectTypeSelectionView()`

**Step-by-Step Instructions:**

1. **Open Home Tab**
   - Tap the circular Home button in the center of the bottom tab bar
   - Ensure you're on the main home screen

2. **Access Create Project**
   - Locate the "+" button in the bottom tab bar (to the left of center)
   - Tap the "+" button

3. **Choose Creation Method**
   - **Option A: AI-Assisted**
     - Tap "Using AI" or "AI Assistant" button
     - You'll see a conversational AI interface
     - Describe your project in natural language
     - AI will ask clarifying questions if needed
     - Review AI-generated project details
     - Edit any fields if necessary
     - Tap "Submit" or "Create Project"
   
   - **Option B: Manual**
     - Tap "Manually" or "Manual Entry" button
     - Fill out the project form:
       - **Title**: Enter project name
       - **Description**: Describe what you need
       - **Category**: Select service type
       - **Address**: Enter project location (required)
       - **Budget**: Enter total budget amount
       - **Duration**: Estimated time in days
     - **Add Phases** (optional):
       - Tap "Add Phase" button
       - Enter phase name, budget, duration
       - Repeat for multiple phases
     - **Upload Photos** (optional):
       - Tap photo upload area
       - Select images from gallery
     - Tap "Submit" or "Create Project"

4. **After Creation**
   - Project appears in "My Projects" tab
   - Status will be "Pending" (waiting for bids)
   - You'll receive notifications when bids arrive

**Common Questions:**
- **"Can I edit after creating?"** ‚Üí Yes, go to My Projects ‚Üí Tap project ‚Üí Edit button
- **"What if I don't know the budget?"** ‚Üí Use AI assistant, it will estimate
- **"Can I add phases later?"** ‚Üí Yes, edit project and add phases

---

### Viewing My Projects

**Navigation Path:**
```
"My Projects" tab (bottom right) OR Home tab ‚Üí My Projects section
```

**View Components:**
- Main View: `AllUserProjectsView()` (set `selectedTab = .myProjects`)
- Project Details: `ProjectStatusTimelineView(projectId: String, isServiceProvider: false)`
- Filters: Available in `AllUserProjectsView()` (All, Pending, Active, Completed)

**Step-by-Step Instructions:**

1. **Access Projects**
   - **Method 1**: Tap "My Projects" tab in bottom tab bar (right side)
   - **Method 2**: From Home tab, scroll to "My Projects" section

2. **Filter Projects**
   - At top of screen, you'll see filter tabs:
     - **All**: Shows all projects
     - **Pending**: Projects waiting for bids
     - **Active**: Projects in progress
     - **Completed**: Finished projects
   - Tap desired filter to view specific status

3. **View Project Details**
   - Tap any project card
   - You'll see:
     - Project timeline with status indicators
     - Phase breakdown
     - Budget information
     - Bids (if any)
     - Contract status
     - Edit options

4. **Project Actions**
   - **Edit Project**: Tap "Edit" button
   - **View Bids**: Tap "View Bids" (if status is "Bid Received")
   - **Approve Bid**: Tap "Accept" on a bid
   - **Sign Contract**: Tap "Sign Contract" button
   - **Make Payment**: Tap "Pay" on a phase
   - **Add Address**: Tap "Add Address" if missing

**Common Questions:**
- **"Why can't I see my project?"** ‚Üí Check filter - try "All" filter
- **"How do I know if I have bids?"** ‚Üí Status changes to "Bid Received", notification sent
- **"Where is my contract?"** ‚Üí Tap project ‚Üí Scroll to Contract section

---

### Finding Service Providers

**Navigation Path:**
```
Home tab ‚Üí Service Providers section ‚Üí Tap service card OR "All services"
```

**View Components:**
- Service Providers List: `ServiceProvidersView(selectedService: serviceCategory)`
- All Services: `PickServiceView()`
- Technician Profile: `TechUserProfileView(technicianId: Int)`
- Search Results: `FloatingSearchResultsView` (embedded in `HomeView`)

**Step-by-Step Instructions:**

1. **Access Service Providers**
   - Open Home tab (center button)
   - Scroll to "Service Providers" section
   - You'll see horizontal scrollable row of service cards

2. **Browse by Category**
   - Scroll horizontally through service cards
   - Each card shows:
     - Service icon/logo
     - Service name
   - Tap any service card to see technicians for that service

3. **View All Services**
   - Tap "All services" button (next to "Service Providers" title)
   - Opens full services grid view
   - Shows all available service categories
   - Tap any service to see providers

4. **Search for Services**
   - Use search bar at top of Home screen
   - Toggle search type (Services or Service Providers)
   - Type search query
   - Results appear below
   - Tap result to view

5. **View Service Provider Profile**
   - After selecting a service, you'll see list of technicians
   - Tap technician card to view:
     - Portfolio
     - Past projects
     - Ratings
     - Contact options
     - Book Appointment button

**Common Questions:**
- **"How do I contact a provider?"** ‚Üí Tap provider ‚Üí Chat button or Book Appointment
- **"Can I see their work?"** ‚Üí Tap provider ‚Üí View Portfolio section
- **"What services are available?"** ‚Üí Tap "All services" to see complete list

---

### Booking an Appointment

**Navigation Path:**
```
Service Provider Profile ‚Üí "Book Appointment" button
```

**View Components:**
- Technician Profile: `TechUserProfileView(technicianId: Int)`
- Booking: `bookingView()` or appointment booking sheet (embedded in TechUserProfileView)

**Step-by-Step Instructions:**

1. **Find Service Provider**
   - Navigate to service provider (see "Finding Service Providers" above)
   - Tap on provider card

2. **Access Booking**
   - On provider profile, locate "Book Appointment" button
   - Tap the button

3. **Select Date**
   - Calendar picker appears
   - Navigate to desired month
   - Tap on date

4. **Select Time**
   - Time slots appear
   - Tap available time slot

5. **Add Details** (optional)
   - Enter project description if applicable
   - Add any notes

6. **Confirm**
   - Review date, time, details
   - Tap "Confirm" or "Book Appointment"
   - Appointment saved

7. **View Appointment**
   - Go to Appointments tab
   - Appointment appears in "Upcoming" filter
   - Tap to view details or reschedule

**Common Questions:**
- **"Can I cancel?"** ‚Üí Yes, Appointments tab ‚Üí Tap appointment ‚Üí Cancel
- **"How do I reschedule?"** ‚Üí Appointments tab ‚Üí Tap appointment ‚Üí Reschedule
- **"Will I get reminder?"** ‚Üí Yes, notification sent before appointment

---

### Approving Bids

**Navigation Path:**
```
My Projects tab ‚Üí Tap project with "Bid Received" status ‚Üí View Bids ‚Üí Accept
```

**View Components:**
- Project View: `ProjectStatusTimelineView(projectId: String, isServiceProvider: false)`
- Bids Section: Embedded in `ProjectStatusTimelineView` (shows `BidReceivedStatusView`)
- Accept Action: Handled within `ProjectStatusTimelineView`

**Step-by-Step Instructions:**

1. **Check for Bids**
   - Go to My Projects tab
   - Look for projects with "Bid Received" status
   - Notification badge may appear

2. **Open Project**
   - Tap project card with "Bid Received" status
   - Project details open

3. **View Bids**
   - Scroll to "Bids" section
   - Tap "View Bids" button
   - List of all bids appears

4. **Review Bid Details**
   - Each bid shows:
     - Service provider name
     - Proposed price
     - Estimated duration
     - Notes/comments
   - Compare multiple bids

5. **Accept Bid**
   - Tap "Accept" button on desired bid
   - Confirm acceptance
   - Project status changes to "Approved"
   - Contract becomes available

6. **After Acceptance**
   - Service provider notified
   - Project moves to "Active" status
   - Can proceed to contract signing

**Common Questions:**
- **"Can I reject a bid?"** ‚Üí Yes, simply don't accept it, or accept another bid
- **"What if I want to negotiate?"** ‚Üí Contact provider via chat before accepting
- **"How long do I have?"** ‚Üí Bids remain until you accept or project is cancelled

---

### Signing Contract

**Navigation Path:**
```
My Projects ‚Üí Tap project with "Approved" status ‚Üí "Sign Contract" button
```

**View Components:**
- Project View: `ProjectStatusTimelineView(projectId: String, isServiceProvider: false)`
- Contract Section: `ContractStatusView` (embedded in ProjectStatusTimelineView)
- Signing: Digital signing handled within `ProjectStatusTimelineView` using `DigitalSigningService`

**Step-by-Step Instructions:**

1. **Prerequisites**
   - Project must have "Approved" status
   - A bid must have been accepted
   - All phases must be approved (if applicable)

2. **Access Contract**
   - Go to My Projects tab
   - Find project with "Approved" status
   - Tap project card

3. **Initiate Signing**
   - Scroll to Contract section
   - Tap "Sign Contract" button
   - Contract PDF opens

4. **Review Contract**
   - Read contract terms
   - Check project details
   - Verify phases and pricing
   - Scroll through all pages

5. **Sign Contract**
   - Digital signature tool appears
   - Draw signature or use typed signature
   - Confirm signature
   - Submit

6. **After Signing**
   - Both parties receive email notification
   - Contract status updates to "Signed"
   - Project status changes to "Contract" or "Active"
   - Work can begin

7. **Download Contract**
   - After signing, "Download PDF" button appears
   - Tap to save contract to device
   - PDF includes both signatures

**Common Questions:**
- **"What if I need to change something?"** ‚Üí Contact support or service provider before signing
- **"Can I cancel after signing?"** ‚Üí Review contract terms, may require cancellation process
- **"Where is my signed contract?"** ‚Üí My Projects ‚Üí Tap project ‚Üí Contract section ‚Üí Download

---

### Making Payments

**Navigation Path:**
```
My Projects ‚Üí Tap project ‚Üí Phase section ‚Üí "Pay" button
```

**Step-by-Step Instructions:**

1. **Access Project**
   - Go to My Projects tab
   - Tap project that's in "Active" or "Contract" status

2. **View Phases**
   - Scroll to "Phases" section
   - See list of all project phases
   - Each phase shows:
     - Phase name
     - Budget amount
     - Status (Pending, In Progress, Payment Required, Paid, Completed)

3. **Find Phase Requiring Payment**
   - Look for phase with "Payment Required" status
   - This means service provider completed the phase
   - Payment is needed before next phase can start

4. **Make Payment**
   - Tap "Pay" button on the phase
   - Payment form opens
   - Enter payment details:
     - Payment method
     - Card information (if applicable)
     - Amount (pre-filled)
   - Review payment
   - Tap "Confirm Payment"

5. **After Payment**
   - Phase status changes to "Paid"
   - Service provider can mark phase as "Completed"
   - Next phase can begin
   - Receipt sent via email

6. **View Payment History**
   - In project view, scroll to "Payments" section
   - See all completed payments
   - Download receipts

**Common Questions:**
- **"When do I pay?"** ‚Üí After each phase is completed by service provider
- **"Can I pay in advance?"** ‚Üí Typically pay per phase as work completes
- **"What payment methods?"** ‚Üí Check payment form for available options

---

### Managing Appointments

**Navigation Path:**
```
Appointments tab (bottom right in tab bar)
```

**Step-by-Step Instructions:**

1. **Access Appointments**
   - Tap "Appointments" tab in bottom tab bar (right side)
   - Appointments screen opens

2. **View Calendar**
   - Calendar widget at top shows current month
   - Dates with appointments are highlighted
   - Tap date to filter appointments

3. **Filter Appointments**
   - Filter tabs below calendar:
     - **Today**: Today's appointments only
     - **Pending**: Awaiting confirmation
     - **Upcoming**: Future appointments
     - **Completed**: Past appointments
   - Tap filter to view specific category

4. **View Appointment Details**
   - Tap any appointment card
   - See:
     - Project/service description
     - Date and time
     - Address/location
     - Status
     - Total amount (if applicable)

5. **Appointment Actions**
   - **Reschedule**: Tap appointment ‚Üí Reschedule ‚Üí Select new date/time
   - **Cancel**: Tap appointment ‚Üí Cancel ‚Üí Confirm
   - **View on Map**: Tap address to open in maps app
   - **Contact Provider**: Tap provider name ‚Üí Chat

6. **Create New Appointment**
   - From service provider profile ‚Üí Book Appointment
   - (See "Booking an Appointment" section)

**Common Questions:**
- **"How do I get reminder?"** ‚Üí Notifications sent automatically before appointment
- **"Can I change time?"** ‚Üí Yes, use Reschedule option
- **"What if provider cancels?"** ‚Üí You'll receive notification, can book new time

---

## üîß Service Provider Help Guides

### Creating Portfolio

**Navigation Path:**
```
Home tab ‚Üí "Create Portfolio" button (purple button above Available Projects)
```

**View Components:**
- Create Portfolio: `CreatePortfolioView()`
- Trigger: Button in `HomeContentView` (service provider home)

**Step-by-Step Instructions:**

1. **Access Create Portfolio**
   - Open Home tab (service provider home)
   - Look for purple "Create Portfolio" button
   - Button appears above "Available Projects" section
   - Only visible if you don't have a portfolio yet

2. **View Information**
   - Tap "Create Portfolio" button
   - Information screen appears
   - Read benefits and instructions
   - Tap "Create Portfolio" to proceed

3. **Fill Portfolio Form**
   - **Bio/Description**:
     - Enter professional description
     - Describe your experience and expertise
     - Minimum characters may be required
   
   - **Years of Experience**:
     - Tap experience picker
     - Select number of years
     - Scroll to find your experience level
   
   - **Certificates**:
     - Tap "Upload Certificates"
     - Select photos from gallery
     - Can upload multiple certificates
     - Ensure photos are clear and readable
   
   - **Select Regions**:
     - Tap "Select Regions"
     - Choose service areas
     - Can select multiple regions
     - "Select All" option available

4. **Submit Portfolio**
   - Review all information
   - Ensure all required fields filled
   - Tap "Submit" button
   - Portfolio sent for admin approval

5. **Wait for Approval**
   - Status changes to "Waiting for Approval"
   - Admin reviews portfolio
   - Notification sent when approved
   - Portfolio becomes public

6. **After Approval**
   - Portfolio visible to users
   - Can add past projects
   - Can generate PDF portfolio
   - Can edit portfolio details

**Common Questions:**
- **"How long for approval?"** ‚Üí Typically 1-3 business days
- **"Can I edit after submission?"** ‚Üí Yes, after approval, go to Profile ‚Üí My Portfolio
- **"What if rejected?"** ‚Üí You'll receive notification with reason, can resubmit

